posts.subject: CLICK [SEED] NEXT TO IMAGES
posts.body:
==AND KEEP ZERONET OPEN==
It's just like torrents, you don't seed, then shit dies. If you only post and fuck off no one is going to be able to save the image, at most you'll be able to see the thumbnails, but the actual images are dead because you posted and closed the browser/zeronet before anyone could save and seed it too.

So click [seed] for your lolicon refugees.

posts.subject: Seeding Images
posts.body: Hey Acid, is there a warning a you can put up for people to click [Seed] on images that they see? Obviously , the text, CSS, and thumbnails are saved and seeded/distributed fine since just lurking a thread will make you see them and hence save and help distribute them. But a lot of full images are dead because no one saved them and or the poster who was the only seeder left before anyone could save and become seeders themselves. This feels like a massive problem. Censorship-resistent-wise the site seems fines, but content delivery and storage seems like it'll be awful unless more anons are willing to click [Seed] on images.

>>3621202c-ba4f-4115-bf3d-54995313c676
Options on the top left corner of 08chan gives you a list of blacklisted users.

Click on the Zeronet button on the top right to take you to the Zeronet homepage. Next to "Hello Zeronet_" are three vertical dots. Click it open a drop down menu. Scroll down until you see "Manage Blocked Users and Sites".
